module implementation

%  in ubuntu to get modules we need to install docker
%  install docker
sudo apt update
sudo apt install docker.io -y
%  enable and start docker 
sudo systemctl enable docker
sudo systemctl start docker
%  run redis stack 
sudo docker run -d --name redis-stack -p 6379:6379 -p 8001:8001 redis/redis-stack:latest

Redis will run on localhost:6379
RedisInsight (GUI) will run on localhost:8001


% if already a server running 
sudo systemctl stop redis-server
 sudo systemctl disable redis-server
  or 
  sudo docker rm -f redis-stack
%  then again run 
sudo docker run -d --name redis-stack -p 6379:6379 -p 8001:8001 redis/redis-stack:latest


Module	Purpose
RedisJSON	Store, update, and query JSON documents.
RediSearch	Full-text search, secondary indexing, and querying.
RedisGraph	Graph database with Cypher-like queries.
RedisTimeSeries	Efficiently handle time-series data for metrics/logs.
RedisBloom	Probabilistic data structures (Bloom filter, Cuckoo filter).
RedisAI	  Store and run machine learning models.




